The startle reflex is a reaction in the brain that kicks the body into immediate action to protect itself, bypassing all conscious thought. This has evolved to happen VERY quickly following the sudden dangerous stimulus (aka sounds of a certain volume), while stimuli that don\'t trigger this reflex don\'t elicit as quick a reaction time.
